cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.MA, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with the interference created by cognitive radios in a network, which is a key issue in the field of wireless communication and networking. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the deployment of cognitive radios, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of analytical formulae and Monte Carlo simulations suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
